list_page_teaser: Long ago and far away I was hired by one boss, who liked me, then transferred to work for a different boss, who didn't like me.  Contrast the images of these two bosses with one of my Self-Portraits.
description_html: This gallery contains images of a couple of my bosses at a job I had long long ago in a place far far away. One of them liked me, and the other did not.
story_html:
It's definitely not easy to work for a boss who doesn't like you! I eventually learned from a third manager that these two argued a lot.

I do not feel it would be appropriate to share either of their names, and I hope this minimal story is enough to add context to the images, which show a fairly large contrast between the two people, despite the fact that both are 'xNFx's.

image_list.title: Manager A
image_list.gallery_page_teaser: A portrait like this, that has a mix of colors, usually indicates a well-rounded individual.  (The exception is when the image is based on just a four-letter-type and hence fixed percentages).  Click on the image to learn more.
image_list.story_html: Once upon a time long long ago in a faraway place I was hired by Manager A. After about three months the department reorganized and I found myself working for Manager B. It turned out to be a challenging job, sometimes I felt I could not do anything right! Much later, I found out from Manager C that Manager A and Manager B argued a lot. Then I remembered that Manager A had hired me while Manager B was on vacation!!  This is an image of Manager A, who was very friendly to me.
image_list.explain_dom: In Extraverts, the dominant function is directed outwardly.
image_list.explain_aux: In Extraverts, the auxiliary function is directed inwardly and is less evident than the dominant function.

image_list.title: Manager B
image_list.subtitle_html: A Boss Who Didn't Like Me
image_list.gallery_page_teaser: A portrait like this, that has a preponderance of a single color, indicates someone who is strong in one area, but as a result of this focused strength, weak in others.  Click on the image to learn more.
image_list.story_html: Once upon a time long long ago in a faraway place I was hired by Manager A. After about three months the department reorganized and I found myself working for Manager B. It turned out to be a challenging job, sometimes I felt I could not do anything right! Much later, I found out from Manager C that Manager A and Manager B argued a lot. Then I remembered that Manager A had hired me while Manager B was on vacation!!  The red in this image of Manager B makes it obvious to me that, Manager B had such strong feelings and after the reorg I never really had a chance.
image_list.explain_dom: In Introverts, the dominant function is directed inwardly.
image_list.explain_aux: In Introverts, the auxiliary function is directed outwardly and is more evident than the dominant function.
